    <h2>: Attempt all the questions.</h2><h3>Question 1</h3>
<div><p><p>What is “subject verb agreement” in a sentence? Why is this agreement necessary in any type of writing? Explain it with at least three examples.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><strong>Subject-verb agreement</strong> is a grammatical rule that states that the subject and verb in a sentence must agree in number. In other words, if the subject is singular, the verb should be singular, and if the subject is plural, the verb should be plural. This agreement is crucial in any type of writing because it helps maintain clarity and grammatical correctness, ensuring that sentences are easily understood and free from errors.</p>
<p>Example 1:</p>
<p>Incorrect: The dog and the cat loves to play together.</p>
<p>Correct: The dog and the cat love to play together.</p>
<p>In this example, the subject &#8220;the dog and the cat&#8221; is plural because it refers to more than one animal. Therefore, the verb &#8220;love&#8221; must also be plural to match the subject. The incorrect version has a singular verb &#8220;loves,&#8221; which creates a subject-verb agreement error</p>
<p>Example 2:</p>
<p>Incorrect: Each of the students are responsible for their own assignments.</p>
<p>Correct: Each of the students is responsible for their own assignments.</p>
<p>In this example, the phrase &#8220;each of the students&#8221; refers to individual students, making the subject singular. Thus, the verb &#8220;is&#8221; should be singular as well. The incorrect version uses the plural verb &#8220;are,&#8221; which is not in agreement with the singular subject.</p>
<p>Example 3:</p>
<p>Incorrect: The book that I borrowed from the library were interesting.</p>
<p>Correct: The book that I borrowed from the library was interesting.</p>
<p>Here, the subject &#8220;the book&#8221; is singular, referring to a single book. Therefore, the verb &#8220;was&#8221; must also be singular to match the subject. The incorrect version uses the plural verb &#8220;were,&#8221; which does not agree with the singular subject.</p>
<p>Subject-verb agreement is necessary in writing to avoid confusion and to maintain grammatical correctness. If this agreement is not followed, sentences may become unclear, and the writing can lose its credibility. Proper subject-verb agreement ensures that sentences are grammatically sound and effectively convey the intended message to the readers.</p>
</div>
